Role Authorization:

Spring has inbuilt interface and classes which are being used for Spring Security.
- GrantedAuthority implemeented by SimpleGrantedAuthority 

@PreAuthoriz, @Secured, 
@PostAuthorize = to filter return objects based on role

E.g: 
@PostAuthorize("returnedObject.owner == authentication.nam")
public Report getReport(Long reportId) {
    return report;
}

@Prefilter and @PostFilter = filter collections or arrays passed as method agruments or returned by method 

Two ways:

1. Method level Security =
- Flexible, 
- ideal for detailed control and complex conditions
-Tightly coupled with business logic

2. Request matchers approach
- URL based 
- ideal for simple and maintainable URL-based security
- Less granularity to method-level security

=> can use Combination of both 
